o estimated that perhaps a third of Arambourgiana's total\nmass was in its head and neck. Is it possible to reconstruct an azhdarchid\n(scale is irrelevant here) such that cM and cP line up? Subsidiary question:\nif I understood Palmer's paper on headcrests correctly (and I'm not at all\nsure I did) the head itself, especially held at the downward angle that many\nresearchers think they were, would generate some lift. Act, in effect, as a\nsort of canard. I'd be anxious to know your thoughts on these questions.\n\nReplyDelete\n\nReplies\n\nReply\n\n  21. taazeem29 September 2021 at 10:19\n\nThis comment has been removed by a blog administrator.\n\nReplyDelete\n\nReplies\n\nReply\n\n  22. Anonymous12 March 2022 at 20:49\n\nThis comment has been removed by a blog administrator.\n\nReplyDelete\n\nReplies\n\nReply\n\nAdd comment\n\nLoad more...\n\nNewer Post Older Post Home\n\nSubscribe to: Post Comments (Atom)\n\n## Visit MarkWitton.co.uk\n\n## Become a Patron\n\n## Who is this 'Mark Witton' chap?\n\nMark Witton\n\n    Dr Mark Witton is a palaeontologist and palaeoartist, affiliated with the University of Portsmouth, UK. My technical research is focused on pterosaurs - Mesozoic flying reptiles - but my artwork has introduced me to a wide array of different fossil animals that are just as interesting. I work as a freelance author, consultant and artist: check out my work at MarkWitton.co.uk, follow me on Twitter @MarkWitton, and browse my books here. Contact me at wittonprints[at]gmail.com. Due to volume of email I can't always reply to messages, but I do my best.\n\nView my complete profile\n\nTweets by @MarkWitton\n\n## Follow me on Pinterest\n\nMark WittonMark Witton PaleoartFollow On\n\n## Subscribe To\n\nPosts\n\nAtom\n\nPosts\n\nComments\n\nAtom\n\nComments\n\n## Search This Blog\n\n## Blog Archive\n\n  * \u25ba 2023 (4)\n\n    * \u25ba May (1)\n    * \u25ba March (1)\n    * \u25ba February (1)\n    * \u25ba January (1)\n\n  * \u25ba 2022 (12)\n\n    * \u25ba Dece